# SnapTrash Core Project Rules

**This rule is always active** when working in the SmartWaste/SnapTrash repository.

## Mandatory Context
- Read and internalize `DETAILED-OVERVIEW.md` (repo structure, complete data flow, setup) and `snaptrash-plan.md` (architecture, stages, tables) on every session.
- **Critical**: The barcode_visible feature and all manufacturer ID extraction (GS1, ZXing, text_visible brand matching, "Dart Container" references) have been **completely removed**. Do not reintroduce them. Plastic analysis is visual + EPA only.
- Use the `snaptrash`, `databricks-snaptrash`, `firecrawl-snaptrash`, and `ui-ux-snaptrash` project skills for detailed guidance on pipelines, Databricks jobs, scraping, dashboard UI/UX (with Framer Motion + 21st.dev), schemas, and workflows.

## Architecture & Data Flow (Never Break)
1. **Frontend** (React/Vite/TS/Tailwind/Mapbox/Recharts) â†’ camera upload â†’ POST /scan â†’ polls insights/locality every ~5s. Two-column results (food left, plastic right with severity badges), charts, map, gamification.
2. **Ingestion** (FastAPI in `apps/ingestion/`): S3 â†’ Groq Vision (clean JSON without barcode/manufacturer) â†’ `food_analysis.py` (USDA-style lookups + contamination logic: decay_stage>=4 or mold_visible â†’ contaminated=True, compostable=False) + `plastic_analysis.py` (resinâ†’polymer, EPA harmful/banned) â†’ `ScanRow` (Pydantic from common) â†’ Databricks `snaptrash.scans`.
3. **Analytics** (`apps/analytics/`): Loads MSW Dryad + Firecrawl data â†’ SQL aggregations, Prophet forecasts (MLflow), thresholds â†’ `insights`, `locality_agg`, `enzyme_alerts`. Readers expose data to API/frontend.
4. **Shared** (`packages/common/`): Schemas, tables DDL, Databricks client, env settings. **Only coupling point** between apps.

## Monorepo & Tooling Rules
- Use `uv sync` (per-app pyproject.toml installs editable `common` package).
- Python: Strict type hints (Pydantic models), modular services, tests in `tests/`.
- Never duplicate schemas or table definitions â€” always extend `snaptrash_common.*`.
- Frontend: pnpm, functional components, colocate styles, follow modern UX (leverage ui-ux-pro-max skill where relevant).
- Scripts: Prefer `scripts/run_dev.sh`, `bootstrap_databricks.py`, `seed_fake_scans.py`.
- Branches: Work in `dev/ingestion` or `dev/analytics`, integrate to `main`.

## Coding Standards
- **Schemas first**: All DB rows must exactly match `schemas.py` models and `tables.py`.
- **Lookups**: Extend `food_analysis.py` dicts (SHELF_LIFE, PRICE_PER_KG, CO2_PER_KG) or replace with real APIs when improving. Keep fuzzy `_key()` matcher.
- **Databricks**: Use SDK/client from common. Partitioned Delta tables. Keep notebooks in sync.
- **Documentation**: Update `DETAILED-OVERVIEW.md` when architecture changes.
- **MCP**: Use Databricks and Firecrawl MCP servers for live queries/scraping.
- **UI/UX**: Beautiful, responsive dashboard with color-coded badges, charts, map. No breaking changes to results screen layout from the plan.

## When Editing
- Preserve the ingestion â†” analytics contract.
- Add tests for new logic.
- Maintain the "single source of truth" in Databricks.
- If adding features, update the skill/rule files and overview docs.

This rule + the `snaptrash` skill ensures every Grok interaction produces consistent, production-quality contributions aligned with the project's vision, removed features, and technical decisions.

